# gRCAi Client

Client runtime for gRCAi Root Cause Analysis tool. This repository contains only the client-side code that can be safely deployed to customer environments.

## Quick Installation

### Docker Installation (Recommended)

curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yourorg/grcai-client/main/install-docker.sh | bash### Host Installation

curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yourorg/grcai-client/main/install-host.sh | bash## Prerequisites

### Docker Installation
- Docker installed and running
- Network access to Central service

### Host Installation
- Python 3.12+ installed
- Network access to Central service

## Configuration

After installation, you'll need to:

1. Edit `config/initial/initial.yaml` with your environment details
2. Configure hosts, services, and access methods
3. Restart the service/container to apply changes

## Usage

### Docker

# View logs
docker logs -f grcai-client-runtime

# Run CLI command
docker exec -it grcai-client-runtime python main.py collect --environment initial --components os

# Stop/Start
docker stop grcai-client-runtime
docker start grcai-client-runtime### Host

cd grcai-client
./run-ui.sh

# Or manually
source venv/bin/activate
source .env
streamlit run ui/app.py --server.port=8501 --server.address=0.0.0.0## Updating

To update to the latest version, simply re-run the installation script:

# Docker
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yourorg/grcai-client/main/install-docker.sh | bash

# Host
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/yourorg/grcai-client/main/install-host.sh | bash## Support

